    <h3>Syntax Highlighting</h3>
    <p>You can easily provide code that will be automatiacally highlighted.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <p>If you type this:</p>
<pre>
```ruby
class TipsOnRails
  attr_accessor :tips, :bookmarks

  def view_and_learn
    tips + bookmarks
  end

  def post_tip(tip)
    tips << tip
  end
end
```

```html
&lt;div id="tip" class="selected"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;%= user.name %&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```

```css
#tip.selected {
  color: blue;
  font-weight: bold;
  text-decoration: none;
}
```
</pre>        
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <p>You will get this:</p>

